  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for ovmf",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for ovmf fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2026-25833: mbedtls: buffer overflow in the `x509_inet_pton_ipv6()` function (bsc#1261476).\n- CVE-2026-25834: mbedtls: client accepts signature algorithm chosen by server even if not advertised in client hello\n  (bsc#1261477).\n- CVE-2026-25835: mbedtls: no pseudo-random number generator reseed when cloning an application (bsc#1261478).\n- CVE-2026-34874: mbedtls: NULL pointer dereference in distinguished name parsing (bsc#1261469).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
